text: Tortang kalabasa, also known as squash fritters, is a Filipino omelette made by mixing mashed or finely-grated calabaza with flour, water, egg, salt, and pepper. Other ingredients like minced vegetables can also be added. It is very similar to okoy, but does not use shrimp. Regardless it is sometimes known as squash okoy or okoy na kalabasa. ==See also== *Tortang talong *Poqui poqui ==References== ==External links== Category:Omelettes Category:Philippine cuisine
title: Tortang kalabasa
